    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 ripe mangoes, peeled and diced</li>
            <li>2 cups cold water</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons sugar (adjust to taste)</li>
            <li>Ice cubes (optional)</li>
            <li>Mint leaves for garnish (optional)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Place the diced mangoes in a blender.</li>
            <li>Add cold water and sugar to the blender.</li>
            <li>Blend until smooth and the sugar is fully dissolved.</li>
            <li>Strain the mango mixture to remove any fibers, using a fine-mesh sieve or cheesecloth.</li>
            <li>Chill the mango juice in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.</li>
            <li>Serve the mango juice over ice cubes if desired.</li>
            <li>Garnish with mint leaves for a refreshing touch.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your homemade mango juice!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

